Kokonaisuus.IlmoittautumisOhje:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prerequisites:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor&#39;s degree from a University or from a University of Applied Sciences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to complete the studies you must have a good command of English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please also note&lt;/strong&gt; that TERVAL5 Mental health research: Using the knowledge and adding to it (5 ECTS) is completed preferably after TERKAN9 Global Issues on Mental Health and Mental Health Services (5 ECTS)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enrollment&lt;/strong&gt; to autumn 2018 courses starts at Wed 15 August 2018 at 10 am.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The courses have a limited number of places.&amp;nbsp;The places are filled in order of enrollment (on a first come first served basis). There is a quota of 3 for the Open University students, except course &lt;span&gt;Health in disasters, conflicts and complex human emergencies 5 students&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please notice, enrollment to individual course/courses. Name of the course will appear to the application form only when the enrollment period will begin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please sent a copy of the degree certificate&lt;/strong&gt; immediately after the enrollment by post to the address: Tampereen yliopisto, Avoin yliopisto, P&amp;auml;ivi Antinoja, Kampusranta 9 C, 60320 Sein&amp;auml;joki or by email attachment to paivi.antinoja@uta.fi&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Study fee: 15 euros / 1&amp;nbsp;ECTS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enrollment in Open University studies is always binding. You cannot cancel your enrollment and your study fee cannot be reimbursed. You will be billed for your study fee after enrollment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.uta.fi/avoinyliopisto/en/admissions.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Application forms&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.uta.fi/avoinyliopisto/en/fees.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;study fees&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Degree students of the University of Tampere&lt;/strong&gt; can&amp;rsquo;t enroll through the enrollment system of Open University&lt;/p&gt;

Kokonaisuus.Kuvaus:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prerequisites:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor&#39;s degree from a University or from a University of Applied Sciences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to complete the courses you must have a good command of English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TERVAL5 Mental Health Research: Using the Knowledge and Adding to it (5 ECTS) and TERKAN9 Global Issues on&amp;nbsp;Mental Health and Mental Health Services: (5 ECTS) are carried out completely online.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGHES03 Health in disasters, conflicts and complex human emergencies&amp;nbsp;(3 ECTS) takes place in a classroom setting&amp;nbsp;at the University of Tampere and the l&lt;span&gt;ectures are held in daytime.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

