&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Enrollment to autumn 2018 courses &lt;/b&gt;starts at&amp;nbsp;Wed 15 August 2018 at 10 am.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;Enrollment to spring 2019 courses&lt;/b&gt; starts at&amp;nbsp;Wed 21 Nov 2018 at 10 am.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You&amp;acute;ll find the course on the application form in alphabetical order according to the course code (for example &quot;&lt;b&gt;LFCS01&lt;/b&gt; Perspectives to Sustainable Organisational and Societal Change&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Admission requirements&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Eligible to apply to the MDP in Leadership for Change -advanced studies (Open University Studies) is a person who:&lt;br /&gt;- has completed a university level Bachelor&#39;s degree or equivalent in the field of Administrative Sciences, Business Administration or Political Science/International Relations or other relevant field.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Language requirements&lt;/strong&gt;: see the page &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.uta.fi/admissions/mdp-leadership-change&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.uta.fi/admissions/mdp-leadership-change&lt;/a&gt; (Eligibility / Language requirements)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please send your degree certificate to the study coordinator by the end of the application period&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

Kokonaisuus.Kuvaus:
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;acute;s possible to study &lt;strong&gt;Master&amp;acute;s Degree Programme in Leadership for Change (LFC) &amp;ndash;advanced studies&lt;/strong&gt; as Open University studies.&lt;br /&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://www10.uta.fi/opas/opintoKokonaisuus.htm?rid=16971&amp;amp;lang=en&amp;amp;uiLang=fi&amp;amp;lvv=2017&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;the LFC curriculum (Open University&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Studies consists of Joint Advanced Studies and Specialisation-specific Advanced Studies.&lt;br /&gt;- &lt;em&gt;Joint Advanced Studies&lt;/em&gt;: in Open University in academic Year 2018-2019 courses LFCS01, LFCS02&lt;br /&gt;- &lt;em&gt;Specialisation-specific Advanced Studies:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governance for Sustainable Change&lt;/strong&gt;: in Open University in academic Year 2018-2019&amp;nbsp;course HALJTS04.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Politics in Wider Europe&lt;/strong&gt;: not&amp;nbsp;in Open University in academic Year 2018-2019.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sustainable Business Management&lt;/strong&gt;: in Open University in academic Year 2018-2019 courses KAMMAS99, KATJOS12.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt; Courses taught in&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt; autumn 2018&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LFCS01&lt;/strong&gt; Perspectives to Sustainable Organisational and Societal Change, 3 ECTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HALJTS04&lt;/strong&gt; Public financial management and evolving administrative structures) 5 ECTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KAMMAS99&lt;/strong&gt; Re-Thinking value creation 5 ECTS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt; Courses taught in&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt; spring 2019&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LFCS02&lt;/strong&gt; Research on Society and Organisations 5 ECTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KATJOS12&lt;/strong&gt; Practices of Strategic Leadership 5 ECTS&lt;/p&gt;
